data.title: Philippines at SEA Games 2023: Full list of athletes qualified
data.meta_description: The Philippines will send a contingent of 840 athletes for the SEA Games 2023 in Phnom Penh, Cambodia.
data.text:
The Philippines will be fielding a massive contingent of 846 athletes at the Southeast Asian Games 2023, in Phnom Penh, Cambodia from May 5 to 17.

The Philippines had sent 627 athletes to the 2021 SEA Games held in Hanoi, Vietnam, where they finished fourth overall with a haul of 227 medals - 52 golds, 70 silvers and 105 bronze.

A majority of gold medals came in athletics (26 - five golds, seven silvers and 14 bronze), gymnastics (14 - seven golds, four silvers and three bronze) and dancesports (12 - five golds, five silvers and two bronze)

Some of the top names from the Philippines sports world will be participating in the 32nd edition of the biennial SEA Games in Cambodia. The list includes record-breaking pole vaulter Ernest John Obiena.

Ernest John Obiena holds the Asian record in the men’s pole vault and is a world championships bronze medallist.

The Philippines’ largest teams at the SEA Games 2023 will be in football (93), athletics (50), esports (40) and floorball (38).
